   <head>To the Reader.</head>
   <p>Pag. 235. l. 20. I say, <hi>that Christ obaied the law for him selfe,</hi> not because he did by his obedience merit his own glorie: but because he was to be a perfect and pure high priest, not onely in nature but also in life: and as he was a creature, he was to be conformable to the law.</p>
